budyk (Ukrainian "будик" — alarm clock) is a lightweight, self-contained
server monitoring daemon. Single static binary, no external dependencies,
no database.

Key features:
  * 3-level adaptive collection (L1 heartbeat / L2 watchful / L3 active) —
    the daemon truly sleeps when not needed and wakes up instantly.
  * Tiered ring-buffer storage with CRC32C-protected records.
  * Embedded Lua 5.4 rule engine with sandbox (no io/os/require).
  * Real-time web dashboard with WebSocket catch-up.
  * ncurses-based terminal UI.
  * Argon2id password hashing per OWASP 2024.

